                            <comment id="13096761" author="qwertymaniac" created="Sat, 3 Sep 2011 21:14:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is valid anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For pseudo-distributed mode, due to its generic nature (it applies to both regular and &apos;pseudo&apos; distributed setups), one may use the hbase-daemon.sh to launch the node.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For false-distributed mode, SSH doesn&apos;t seem to be used (HMaster is started as is, on the trigger host.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Please correct me if am wrong, or mark this issue as Not A Problem (now).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
